                            <comment id="13486243" author="tychang" created="Mon, 29 Oct 2012 18:37:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I feel that the bug is different from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7060&quot; title=&quot;Region load balancing by table does not handle the case where a table&amp;#39;s region count is lower than the number of the RS in the cluster&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7060&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7060&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, so I opened this bug seperately. But I will put the fix in the same patch at &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7060&quot; title=&quot;Region load balancing by table does not handle the case where a table&amp;#39;s region count is lower than the number of the RS in the cluster&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7060&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7060&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, if approved. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13492080" author="sershe" created="Wed, 7 Nov 2012 02:46:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the intent is that serversByLoad entries are sorted in ascending order by load (it&apos;s a TreeMap and ServerAndLoad first compares load), therefore it adds entries until it finds the first server over the boundary. So it should be correct... Do you see specific problem because of this code?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13492579" author="tychang" created="Wed, 7 Nov 2012 18:39:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, it missed underloaded servers. This fix has been put int the same patch as the other bug for another region balance bug. The patch has been integrated by Ted. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13492580" author="tychang" created="Wed, 7 Nov 2012 18:40:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the fix is in the same patch as the related bug. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
